extends HibernateGeneralGenericDao

A Hibernate (http://hibernate.org/) based implementation of CompleteGenericDao which can be extended to add more specialized DAO methods.

See the overview for installation/usage tips.

findByExample

public List findByExample(Object exampleObject)
Deprecated. 

Description copied from interface: ByExampleFinder
Find all objects of the type associated with this DAO based on the provided example object and return them in a List. Any non-null properties will be matched exactly and any null values will be ignored.

Note: even though this method accepts any object, you should only give it the associated persistent object type.

Note: If you use primitive types in your persistent objects then those values cannot be null and must be set to something or the example matches will not work the way you expect.
